        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/l/dc4da7/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-10-20T00:32:29.274Z",
        "cooked": "<p>In addition to the delete-feature it would be helpful if we can show that a message we sent has become irrelevant, without hiding the contents for traceability.</p>\n<p>From my experience we use the delete-feature more often for not confusing people with obsolete messages, than for hiding secret content (fortunately). But deleted messages can lead to confusion and unnessesary obscurity.</p>\n<p>E.g. when people answer to group-chat requests privately that then become resolved. Or if i ask a ‚Äúdumb‚Äú question, find the answer and dont want to spam the chat even more with it but want to let poeple konw i answerd this question if they need help.</p>\n<p>Obsolete Messages could just be geyed out visually.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 2,
